    "## 8. Key Findings & Recommendations <a id='8'></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 📌 Summary of Key Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 1. Gender was the single strongest predictor of survival\n",
    "Women survived at **72.7%** vs men at **19.1%**. The \"women and children first\" evacuation protocol is statistically confirmed (χ²=363.2, p<0.001).\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Socioeconomic class had a decisive impact\n",
    "1st class passengers survived at **61.9%** vs 3rd class at **25.5%**. Wealthier passengers had better cabin access, closer proximity to lifeboats, and more information about the emergency.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. Small families had the best survival odds\n",
    "Passengers travelling in groups of 2–4 survived at **56.3%**. Solo travellers (30.3%) and large families (>4 members, 18.3%) fared considerably worse.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 4. Fare is a powerful proxy for privilege\n",
    "Survivors paid a median fare of **£26.00** vs £10.50 for non-survivors. The Mann-Whitney U test confirms this difference is highly significant (p<0.001).\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 5. Cabin information signals survival\n",
